reviews.title: Is there less than 1 star?
reviews.review_text: As I unwrapped the lettuce, I noticed brown spots up and down the lettuce, all through the first half of the head. This is Foxy Romaine Lettuce that I received. Curious, I checked online...found this. A recall of the product that I was sold. https://foxy.com/news/foxy-produce-statement-regarding-the-cdc-romaine-alert Then I searched romaine lettuce brown spots. Evidently they are common and chefs call them rusty spots, The lettuce is "good" but just remove the brown spots. To do that, I had to throw out half of the head. Won't buy again.

reviews.title: Quality romaine, ingeniously packaged
reviews.review_text: A few months ago, I thought I'd take a chance on romaine, again. To my delight, the current producer/wholesaler/retailer partnership has hit it out of the park! Large, fresh, affordable, and reliably in stock. But most especially interesting to me, as a former Produce Dept. Manager, it was ingeniously packaged to maximizing use, while avoiding the dreaded tightrope of dehydration -vs- incipient brown slime. The bag has a loose-fitting "hood" design, which prevents desiccation, without trapping excess moisture, so it "breathes." As I also wrapped the base in a damp paper towel, a head I'd purchased in late November was still crisp and as fresh as the day we'd purchased it, over six weeks later (although much diminished in size).

Actually a less than 1 , even less than minus zero! The size was pitiful. Yet still charged $1.98! I checked to see if would have been charged out per pound @ $1.98. Clearly said EACH. About 4 pcs of lettuce in all. Your shopper should have either asked if still wanted regardless of size or just said OUT OF STOCK.
